title: The Great Bongo Heist
description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

title: I……am Vampier
description: When Vic enters the Monte Macabre film festival, he gets insecure about his artistic vision and decides to copy the work of others, but ultimately learns that staying true to yourself is what's most important.

title: The Fog
description: Victor and Valentino are fed up with Tez. He seems determined to ruin their summer in Monte Macabre. They see no other choice but to leave town for good. But will Tez let them?

title: Hurricane Chata
description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

title: Know It All
description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

title: Bone Bike
description: Victor and Valentino must tame a wild, living motorcycle made of bones, to win Mic and Hun's Underworld grand-prix: The Muerto Race!

title: Stolen Retriever
description: When Vic cooks up a scheme to "borrow" people's dogs and return them for reward money, he gets in over his head with disastrous results!

title: It Grows
description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

title: Fistfull of Balloons
description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

title: Suerte
description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

title: Folk Art Friends
description: When Vic and Val accidentally release some mischievous alebrije spirits, they must enlist the help of master mischief-maker HueHue to help catch them.

title: On Nagual Hill
description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

title: Showdown At Mayahuel Garden
description: When Victor, Valentino, Charlene and Pineapple get separated from their grandmothers, Chata and Maria Teresa are forced to put aside their rivalry and work together to reunite with their grandchildren.

title: The Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

title: Aluxes
description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

title: A New Don
description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

title: My Fair Achi
description: V&V enter Achi in a dog show competition to win a golden trophy, but their overbearing ways drive Achi to the edge.

title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

title: El Silbon
description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

title: Miguelito the Mosquito
description: When Miguelito begins to outshine Victor as the town daredevil, Vic attempts to sabotage him in order to bring the attention back to himself.

title: Churro Kings
description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

title: Forever Ever
description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

title: Another Don
description: When Chata's most precious heirloom goes missing, Victor, Valentino and Isabella are on the case to find out who stole it!

title: Carmelita
description: Chata loans Xochi a car under the condition that Vic and Val can get rides when they need. However, the car becomes aggressive towards V&V and attacks!

title: My Thirsty Little Monster
description: When Valentino discovers Victor has been hiding a baby vampire bat in the house, Victor must convince his brother that he can handle having a pet.

title: La Catrina
description: Valentino is elated to get an exclusive invite to a performance by the famous singer La Catrina in the Underworld. There is just one problem: the invite is for grown-ups only.

title: Balloon Boys
description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

title: The Babysitter
description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

title: Folk Art Foes
description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

title: Boss For a Day
description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

title: Pokin and Proddin
description: Valentino wins a coveted internship to work in the Tez administration. Initially intending to use his insider status to spy on Tez, Val unexpectedly finds himself enjoying the comradery of office life.

title: Fueygo Fest
description: When Vic and Val throw the biggest kid bash ever, they realize they aren't the party planners they thought they were as things start to fall apart.

title: Cleaning Day
description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

title: There's No V in Team
description: When the children of Monte Macabre create their own underground soccer league, Victor finds an unlikely ally in Isabella.

title: Ener-G-Shoes
description: When Vic uses trickery to buy a pair of super cool sneakers from Maria Teresa's yard sale, the shoes try to walk him to his demise as punishment.

title: Tree Buds
description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

title: Charlene Mania
description: When Vic attempts to have the perfect day off, the town's sudden obsession for Charlene gets in his way.

title: Escaramuza
description: When Val's favorite Escaramuza team loses a member, he convinces Xochi to join the squad. He becomes her coach and will do anything to win the big competition.

title: In Your Own Skin
description: When Valentino is mocked for his lack of style, he's determined to get a designer hoodie to prove he has a sense of fashion, which turns out to be harder than it looks.

title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

title: Tez Breaks Bread
description: When Tez returns to town and invites Chata and the boys to a dinner party, she insists they attend so Victor and Valentino set out to expose him as the evil magician he truly is.

title: The Lonely Haunts Club
description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 1
description: When Vic & Val destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they travel with Sal to Corn Mountain to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they have to shrink to the size of ants, creating all kinds of problems!

title: Victor the Predictor
description: When Victor becomes convinced he has a special talent as a psychic, he decides to use his new mental abilities to counsel those around him - until one piece of advice goes too far.

title: Dead Ringer
description: When Vic doesn't pick Val for his soccer team, Val vows to win with his own squad. But when his team doesn't match up, he resorts to supernatural means to win.

title: Starry Night
description: When Vic and Val embark on a camping trip in the woods, their friends start to act suspicious and strange.

title: Starry Eyes
description: When Isabela goes missing, Victor and Valentino learn that a mysterious creature has been hiding in plain sight! V&V are on the case again!

title: La Cucarachita
description: When Vic's beloved pet cockroach dies, Vic turns to Charlene's dark magic to bring her back to life.

title: The Guest
description: Vic & Val blame each other for eating all the food in the kitchen and making a huge mess! However, they soon discover that a ghost is actually to blame! They enlist the help of Achi to unlock the world of spirits among them and kick the ghost out of their house!

title: Get Your Sea Legs
description: When Victor gets teased for not being able to swim, he befriends a mermaid who offers to help, but at a cost.

title: The Lonely Haunts Club 3: La Llorona
description: When Val sets out to get a little privacy in the woods, Vic is bent on pranking his unsuspecting brother,  that is, until Val goes missing.

title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 2
description: When Victor and Valentino destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they journey to Maíz Mountain with Sal to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they must shrink down to the size of ants and embark on a mythical adventure that they'll never forget!

title: Patolli
description: When Valentino has a hot winning streak at an ancient board game, his beginner's luck gets the best of him until, he meets his match. Will he reign as champion or lose it all?

title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

title: Through the Nine Realms of Mictlan
description: When Victor and Valentino cause their ghost friend Cristina to miss her train to the 9th level of the Underworld, the boys now must guide her on a harrowing journey through the treacherous trials of the first 8 levels of the underworld to reunite Cristina with her family.

title: Finding Posada
description: When Victor and Valentino attempt to win the grand prize of best ofrenda at the Dia de Muertos festival, they enlist the help of legendary artist Jose Guadalupe Posada himself!

title: Band For Life
description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

title: Kindred Spirits
description: When Val becomes friends with the ghost of a silent film star, their friendship turns out to have dire consequences.

title: Tez Says
description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

title: Ghosted
description: Vic makes a ghost friend but when she interferes with his shot at being part of the cool kids' Tlatchtli team, he must choose between the two.

title: Love at First Bite
description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

title: Los Pajaros
description: When Valentino trades Huitzi's gifts for one of his own, the birds in town start to turn on him.

title: Cenote Seekers
description: When Vic and Val are running too late to get a ride from Xochi to a fun water park cenote on a particularly hot day, they instead take their bikes. But they wind up lost in the desert and start to hallucinate while blaming each other for getting into this mess.

title: Butterman!
description: When Tez threatens to destroy the town's butterfly habitat to build a bowling alley, Victor, Valentino and Sal must find the Butterman in order to save the butterflies!

title: Decoding Valentino
description: When Val goes on an adventure with Isabella to decode an ancient language, he has to come to terms with the fact that Isabella is smarter in order to save himself.

title: Lords of Ghost Town
description: When V&V recruit a ghost to scare away a bully, they end up messing with the realm of the dead, which has disastrous consequences.

title: Guillermo's Girlfriend
description: Vic & Val try to cheer up a heartbroken Guillermo by reuniting him with his lost love.

title: PuzzleMaster
description: Victor, Valentino, Charlene and Pineapple awaken to find themselves in a bizarre and scary series of puzzle rooms where the rules are simple: escape or cease to exist!

title: Plan-De-Monium
description: Val has meticulously planned for the perfect day of activities with Isabella, but his rigid insistence on sticking to the itinerary make for a less than perfect experience.

title: Escape From Bebe Bay
description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

title: Las Pesadillas
description: When Vic and Val experience a mysterious nightmare that turns deadly, they realize they must stop a sinister force from enchanting them to sleep forever.

title: Go With the Flow
description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

title: The Matchmaker
description: When Val starts a romantic match-making service, he struggles being true to his own feelings for his secret crush.

title: Oddities
description: When a mysterious carnival barker fuses V&V together, they must find a way to come unstuck.

title: The Dark Room
description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

title: The Collector
description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

title: Brotherly Love
description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

title: Baby Pepito
description: When a mysterious "baby" appears on Chata's doorstep, V&V are convinced it's not what it seems.

title: Pastry Peril
description: When Vic must pay off the debt he incurred at Lupe's bakery, he has no choice but to work under his rival's close supervision.

title: Guillermo's Gathering
description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

title: Los Cadejos
description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

title: Poacher Patrol
description: When Don bestows Val the responsibility of patrolling the lake, Val takes it too far and stops who he believes to be a poacher -- with disastrous consequences.

title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

title: The Bodyguard
description: When Don becomes part of Tez's Jaguar Patrol squad, Victor and Valentino are determined to get him fired by any means necessary.

title: Cat-Pocalypse
description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

title: Sal's Our Pal
description: When Victor and Valentino learn Tez has appointed himself the town leader "Huey Tlatoani" of Monte Macabre, they set out to un-seat him with the help of everyone's pal, Sal.

title: La Planchada
description: When Vic gets the chicken pox and is forbidden from playing in a tag tournament, he summons a mythical ghost nurse to cure him.

title: Jump Scare
description: When Victor starts to feel left out because Valentino and Isabella are hanging out without him, he becomes determined get the trio's old dynamic back, even if it means souring their relationship!

title: Old Man Teo
description: When Vic and Val are tasked to volunteer at an Old Folks' Home, Val becomes buddies with the oldest, crankiest person in Monte Macabre and helps him reclaim his youthful power.

title: Villainy In Monte Macabre
description: In a crossover episode with the show Villainous, V&V team up with Dr. Flug and Demencia to try to find a squid monster who is disguised as a human in Monte Macabre.

title: Los Perdidos
description: When Vic joins a group of nighttime skaters called Los Perdidos, Val becomes suspicious of Vic's strange, new, vampire-like behavior.

title: Cuddle Monster
description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

title: El Bigote
description: When Victor lands an internship with Lucha legend El Bigote, he picks up some bad habits that start to affect his life at home.

title: An Evening with Mic and Hun
description: Using their tickets to spend an "Evening with Mic & Hun" to get out of having dinner with Chata's comadres, Victor and Valentino get more than they bargained for, a terrifying dinner party game where losing means a permanent stay in the Underworld!

title: The Cupcake Man
description: When Victor's bad behavior gets out of control, Chata sends him to the one man in town who can set him straight, The Cupcake Man.
